  ('CEREBRAL VESSELS','cerebral_vessels','ANATOMY OF THE NERVOUS SYSTEM','physiologic stenosis ← inertial forces of blood flow diverting main-flow stream from dilated proximal part of ICA with thinner media + thicker adventitia containing many largest branch of ICA arising lateral to optic chiasm major drainage pathway from cerebral veins into internal jugular veins; enclosed by SUPERFICIAL CORTICAL VEINS great variability in drainage territories DEEP CEREBRAL VEINS centripetal drainage of hemispheric white matter and basal ganglia','shares waveform characteristics of both internal + external carotid arteries','lateral to upper border of thyroid cartilage; at level of C3-4 intervertebral disk','{"Location": "lateral to upper border of thyroid cartilage; at level of C3-4 intervertebral disk", "Frequency": "~ 1%", "Histo": "NO smooth muscle / venous valves → bidirectional flow", "Prevalence": "66% (↑ in number + conspicuity with age)"}','{"shares waveform characteristics of both internal + external carotid arteries","CHARACTERISTIC bilateral paramedian thalamic infarcts ± midbrain involvement","velocity increases toward the aorta (9 cm/sec for each cm of distance from the carotid","stagnant eddy that rotates at outer vessel margin","traverses internal auditory canal (with CN VIII)"}','{"general": ["shares waveform characteristics of both internal + external carotid arteries", "velocity increases toward the aorta (9 cm/sec for each cm of distance from the carotid", "stagnant eddy that rotates at outer vessel margin", "CHARACTERISTIC bilateral paramedian thalamic infarcts ± midbrain involvement", "traverses internal auditory canal (with CN VIII)", "traverses hypoglossal canal (with CN XII)", "short wide connection between the cavernous portion of ICA + basilar artery", "penetrates sella turcica (in 50%)", "enlargement of ipsilateral ICA", "ectopic vessel crossing the pontine cistern to anastomose with basilar artery", "traverses foramen magnum", "luminal surface of tria