  ('DANDY-WALKER MALFORMATION','dandy_walker_malformation','CENTRAL NEUROCYTOMA','characterized CLASSICALLY by continuum of anomalies, including Dandy-Walker malformation + Dandy-Walker variant + developing normal rhombencephalon during 1st trimester','large skull ← hydrocephalus + dolichocephaly','disproportionately large expanded posterior fossa','{"Incidence": "12% of all congenital hydrocephaly", "Genetics": "sporadic occurrence; 1-5% risk of recurrence", "Path": "defect in vermis connecting an ependyma-lined retrocerebellar cyst with 4th ventricle", "Age": "majority < 1 year"}','{"large skull ← hydrocephalus + dolichocephaly","diastatic lambdoid suture","disproportionately large expanded posterior fossa","torcular-lambdoid inversion = upward displacement of tentorium + torcular herophili +","absence / hypoplasia of cerebellar vermis:"}','{"general": ["large skull ← hydrocephalus + dolichocephaly", "diastatic lambdoid suture", "disproportionately large expanded posterior fossa", "torcular-lambdoid inversion = upward displacement of tentorium + torcular herophili +", "absence / hypoplasia of cerebellar vermis:", "superiorly displaced superior vermis cerebelli", "small widely separated ± hypoplastic cerebellar hemispheres ← anterolateral", "large posterior fossa cyst with extension through foramen magnum = diverticulum of", "elevated insertion of tentorium cerebelli", "cerebellar hemispheres in apposition without intervening vermis following shunt procedure", "absence of falx cerebelli", "scalloping of petrous pyramids", "ventriculomegaly (in 72% open communication with 3rd ventricle; in 39% patent 4th", "anterior displacement of pons"], "ANGIO": ["high position of transverse sinus", "elevated great vein of Galen", "elevated posterior cerebral vessels", "anterosuperiorly displaced superior cerebellar arteries above the posterior cerebral", "small / absent PICA with high tonsillar loop", "4th ventricle smaller + better formed", "retrocerebellar cyst smaller", "comm